      • priceByEstablishment

        public static double priceByEstablishment(int MAX,
                                          double cont4,
                                          java.lang.String[] materials,
                                          java.lang.Double[] quantity,
                                          java.lang.Double[] homeCenterPrice,
                                          java.lang.Double[] ferreteriaCentroPrice,
                                          java.lang.Double[] ferreteriaBarrioPrice)
        This method displays the best prices for each material and the establishment with that price.
        pre: The arrays must be filled and MAX has to be greater than 0.
        pre:
        Parameters:
        MAX, - used to iterate through the arrays.
        cont4, - used as a counter to add each of the best prices.
        materials, - used to display the material name and define display its price.
        quantity, - used to find the quantity of each material and therefore, find its price.
        homeCenterPrice, - individual price for each material, used to multiply itself with the quantity to obtain HomeCenter's price for that material
        ferreteriaCentroPrice,individual - price for each material, used to multiply itself with the quantity to obtain Ferreteria del Centro's price for that material
        ferreteriaBarrioPrice - individual price for each material, used to multiply itself with the quantity to obtain Ferreteria del Barrio's price for that material
        Returns:
        cont4, returns the sum of each one of the best prices per material.
